<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-07T19:41:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-07T19:41:00-05:00" n="671" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d671">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/2064</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Tampico</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Tampico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-07T18:00:00-06:41">
                                        <hi rend="italic">August 7, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>With reference to petroleum tax law just republished, oil companies
                                have been warned that persons highly connected with the Mexican
                                Government are prepared to profit from any refusal or failure to
                                comply with its provisions on the ground of their
                                unconstitutionality, by promptly denouncing through third parties
                                valuable oil properties not manifested by present holders within
                                time allowed.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>